column5: Good luck on your trip, let me know how you did. Heading for Lady Lake Evelyn June 5th and then Nipissing in August for 2 weeks. gonna be a fun summer.

32 days (June 23) until we arrive at Lac Seul Lodge and the Black Bay Outpost Camp. I'm bringing my 12 year old son for the first time. I hope he's ready and loves it as much as I do because the XBox Live will be 800+ miles away!
Leaving for the English River (also the Grassy Narrows area) in 20 days, 15 hrs. and 37 mins.!!!
June 22nd we leave for 7 days fishing the NW and SW sections of Lac Seul.
Too darn long for sure. I'll be dunking worms on July 1st this year on Lac Seul and pother nearby bodies of water until the $$$ runs out!! Everyone have a great safe trip! Jim
Today is the day. Will be on the road in about 8 hours. Let the good times roll.
Leaving in 18 Days for O'sullivan lake Quebec... will be spending fathers day with my son's. the best way to spend fathers day....
kingsway2, how did you do on your trip to Marmion? We are heading up 7-18-12 for our annual trip. How high was the water? Could you get through the sluiceway?
Just got back from our annual trip to Cochrane early Monday morning. The weather and fishing could not have been any better, great time!
Where in cochrane? We are going June 22 with COchrane Air Services!!
I and my cousin are leaving early Friday morning for NW Ontario for 2 weeks.Paul
67 days until my sons and I are heading for the SE section of Lac Seul. Staying in Sioux Lookout and trailering to Deception Bay.
be at Dinorwic and the goon. cant wait
28 Days for me, leaving on 6/16 for the English River, Grassy Narrows area
We'll be at Northern Lights Resort, Cedar Lake(good lord willing and the creek don't rise) 26 days from today for our first Canadian adventure.
16 days till we leave for The Woods. Worst 16 days of the year followed by the 10 best.

We are packing Wed 5/23and leaving 5/24 for a 14 day trip to Finlayson Resort and we will fish Finlayson, Marmion lake, and we are looking for suggestions for other lakes in the Antikokan area for Walleye, Northern, Trout, and Perch. We also are looking for good eating (non-wormy) perch fishing so we can bring some home. All help is appreiciated and I will give reports for there from my laptop. Regards, Rich King

We (9 guys) will be at Lac Seul Lodge / Black Bay Outpost Camp on June 9th. This is our groups 28th year there. Headed to Lost Island Lodge on Lac Seul with my wife on June 30. Both of these Lodges offer great service and the fishing is awesome. I pray that all of you that are going to Canada this year have a great time and a SAFE trip. Good. Luck, Mike Kansas Sirmanski

A group of five from Denver, CO leave in six days for Minneapolis. We join five more from Waterloo, IA and make the long drive to Red Lake. From Chimo Air in Red Lake we fly 45mins west to Donald Lake Woodland Caribou National Park. Rip lips for 7 days at beautiful Wamserville Lodge! I've been packed for weeks!!!
Lac Seul in T-minus 12 days. Absolutely can't wait. 2nd trip for my 8 year old son, 1st trip for my 10 year old daughter. Here's to an easy border crossing, good weather, and great fishing
7 days and 4 hours from now I will start my voyage north for my first trip to Red Lake this year. :-) I can hardly wait. How long does anyone else have? I know opener is this weekend up there.
June 2nd I'll be at Dogtooth. Getting the boat ready as I type...
I'll be heading to NW Angle on Lake of the Woods Aug 3 I have 2-1/2 months more to wait. Big Narrows is calling me.
16 days Wabigoon-Dinorwic
6 days I'm going to perrault Falls Ontario Canada Golden Arrow camp to a chain of 27 different lakes
July 21 my wife and I will be at Red Lake.
The week of the 4th we'll be on Wabagoon. Have fun Doug
I'm leaving on the 30th of this month for 2 weeks!
I'm leaving the 24th (this coming Thursday) for Young's Wilderness Camp on LOTW, ten days!! Can't sleep!!!
27 different lakes,wow ..nice trip
